# Revision 14.2 - pre-beta (19 nov 2015)
#
# The below instructions are recommended by the devs to
# build gnome with systemd from source on Slackware
#
# 1. Install bash-completion from extra
#
# root@:~# slackpkg install bash-completion
#
# 2. Now we can actually start with compiling the packages for pam and systemd.
#    There are 2 options.
#    Option 1.- Compile package by package in the order of compile-order document
#    Option 2.- use Dlackware build software to compile them autmatically.
#
# you will need to compile the following groups:
#
# - Systemd
# - Rebuilds
# - gnome-systemd
